#: ../../glossary/useful_information/tutorial-white_balance_lms.rst:17
msgid ""
"In photography (and hence in videos and images) lighting has a profound "
"effect on the scene: from a warm orange of a candlelight to a cold blue in "
"the shadows of a row of houses or in the mountains with a clear, blue sky. "
"The human brain is capable of adjusting these color differences, and a white "
"object is perceived as white even though the lighting gives it a different "
"hue. In a sense, our brain performs an automatic white balance based on "
"objects we know are white: a piece of white paper, porcelain or a bride's "
"white dress."
msgstr ""
"En fotografia (i per tant, en vídeos i imatges) la il·luminació té un efecte "
"profund en l'escena: des d'una taronja càlida d'una espelma a un blau fred a "
"les ombres d'una fila de cases o a les muntanyes amb un cel blau clar. El "
"cervell humà és capaç d'ajustar aquestes diferències de color, i un objecte "
"blanc es percep com a blanc tot i que la il·luminació li dona un to "
"diferent. En certa manera, el nostre cervell realitza un balanç de blancs "
"automàtic basat en objectes que sabem que són blancs: un tros de paper "
"blanc, porcellana o el vestit blanc d'una núvia."

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/tutorial-white_balance_lms.rst:19
#| msgid ""
#| "A photo or image will show a white or color-neutral object with a hue "
#| "based on the color of the light source(s) and the ambient light, ghiving "
#| "it, at times, a yellow, red, green or blueish tone. Of course, this does "
#| "not look right and needs to be corrected. Ideally, the recording "
#| "equipment has been set to the correct white balance before shooting the "
#| "scene. Most cameras are doing a pretty good job in recognizing the "
#| "lighting situation and make the necessary corrections automatically. But "
#| "when filming, lighting may change during the scene and you don't want "
#| "your camera to automatically and permanently adjust the white balance "
#| "because this is almost impossible to correct in post."
msgid ""
"A photo or image will show a white or color-neutral object with a hue based "
"on the color of the light source(s) and the ambient light, giving it, at "
"times, a yellow, red, green or blueish tone. Of course, this does not look "
"right and needs to be corrected. Ideally, the recording equipment has been "
"set to the correct white balance before shooting the scene. Most cameras are "
"doing a pretty good job in recognizing the lighting situation and make the "
"necessary corrections automatically. But when filming, lighting may change "
"during the scene and you don't want your camera to automatically and "
"permanently adjust the white balance because this is almost impossible to "
"correct in post."
msgstr ""
"Una foto o imatge mostrarà un objecte blanc o de color neutre amb un to "
"basat en el color de la font de llum i la llum ambiental donant, de vegades, "
"un to groc, vermell, verd o blavós. Per descomptat, això no sembla correcte "
"i cal corregir-ho. L'ideal és s'hagi configurat el balanç de blancs correcte "
"a l'equip d'enregistrament abans de filmar l'escena. La majoria de les "
"càmeres fan una bona feina reconeixent la situació d'il·luminació i fent les "
"correccions necessàries automàticament. Però quan es grava, la il·luminació "
"pot canviar durant l'escena i no voleu que la càmera ajusti automàticament i "
"permanentment el balanç de blancs perquè això és gairebé impossible de "
"corregir en la postproducció."

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/tutorial-white_balance_lms.rst:21
msgid ""
"In case your equipment did not set the white balance correctly you can use "
"the :ref:`effects-white_balance` or :ref:`effects-white_balance_lms` effects "
"to eliminate any incorrect hues. In this tutorial we are using the :ref:"
"`effects-white_balance_lms` effect. LMS stands for long, medium and short "
"and is a color space which represents the response of the three types of "
"cones of the human eye, named for the responsiveness (sensitivity) peaks at "
"long, medium, and short wavelengths."
msgstr ""
"En cas que el vostre equip no estableixi correctament el balanç de blancs, "
"podreu utilitzar els efectes :ref:`effects-white_balance` o :ref:`effects-"
"white_balance_lms` per a eliminar qualsevol to incorrecte. En aquesta guia "
"d'aprenentatge utilitzarem l'efecte :ref:`effects-white_balance_lms`. LMS "
"significa llarg, mitjà i curt i és un espai de color que representa la "
"resposta dels tres tipus de cons de l'ull humà, anomenats pels pics de "
"sensibilitat a longituds d'ona llargues, mitjanes i curtes."

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/tutorial-white_balance_lms.rst:29
msgid "White Balance (LMS space) effect"
msgstr "Efecte de balanç de blancs (espai LMS)"

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/tutorial-white_balance_lms.rst:31
msgid ""
"The color picker right next to the :guilabel:`Neutral Color` color panel can "
"be used to select the color that is supposed to be white. Click on it and "
"then select an area in the Project or Clip Monitor by dragging the color "
"picker across. And that is all there is to it!"
msgstr ""
"El selector de color just al costat del plafó de color :guilabel:`Color "
"neutre` es pot utilitzar per a seleccionar el color que se suposa que és "
"blanc. Feu-hi clic i seleccioneu una àrea del monitor del projecte o de "
"clips arrossegant el selector de color. I això és tot el que hi ha!"

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/tutorial-white_balance_lms.rst:35
msgid ""
"Of course, you need a neutral (white) area in your source. If that is not "
"the case you can use the :guilabel:`Color Temperature` slider for some "
"adjustment."
msgstr ""
"Per descomptat, necessiteu una àrea neutra (blanca) a la vostra font. Si "
"aquest no és el cas, podreu utilitzar el control lliscant :guilabel:"
"`Temperatura del color` per a alguns ajustos."

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/tutorial-white_balance_lms.rst:37
msgid ""
"The default value is 6,495. Values above that up to 15,000 make the image "
"\"cooler\"/more blueish, values below up to 1,000 make it \"warmer\"/more "
"amber or orange-y. The values are not true degrees Kelvin (K) but trend "
"towards them."
msgstr ""
"El valor per defecte és 6.495. Els valors superiors a 15.000 fan que la "
"imatge sigui «més freda»/més blava, els valors inferiors a 1.000 la fan «més "
"càlida»/més ambre o taronja. Els valors no són veritables graus Kelvin (K), "
"sinó una tendència cap a ells."

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/tutorial-white_balance_lms.rst:39
msgid ""
"The slider also fine adjusts any color selected with the color picker or the "
"color panel for :guilabel:`Neutral Color` making the image appear warmer or "
"cooler."
msgstr ""
"El control lliscant també ajusta amb precisió qualsevol color seleccionat "
"amb el selector de color o el plafó de color per al :guilabel:`Color "
"neutre`, fent que la imatge aparegui més càlida o freda."

#: ../../glossary/useful_information/tutorial-white_balance_lms.rst:41
msgid ""
"The :ref:`effects-white_balance` effect works the same except that :guilabel:"
"`Color Temperature` is called :guilabel:`Green Tint` which changes the "
"source image from magenta (=0) to green (=10,000). There are cases where you "
"may want to stack both effects and play with the sliders."
msgstr ""
"L'efecte :ref:`effects-white_balance` funciona de la mateixa manera, excepte "
"que la :guilabel:`Temperatura del color` s'anomena :guilabel:`Tint verd`, i "
"que canvia la imatge original des del magenta (=0) al verd (=10.000). Hi ha "
"casos en què voldreu apilar els efectes i jugar amb els controls lliscants."
